From: Nicolas Grunbaum <ngrunbaum@mozilla.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 13:28:27 -0700
Subject: (tmp-cherry-pick) Revert "sdp: introduce MCD::AttributeLevel for
 session/media-level attrs" (5ab65fdd4d)

This reverts commit 60094aab910f7fda6cf40f4334e7369ee4d81a23.

Reason for revert: Breaks downstream projects. The definitions in session_description.h must be kept in parallel until downstream projects are updated.

Original change's description:
> sdp: introduce MCD::AttributeLevel for session/media-level attrs
>
> Generalizes the enum used to track whether an attribute is signalled at
> session level or media level. The previous enum was specific to
> extmap-allow-mixed (ExtmapAllowMixed { kNo, kSession, kMedia }); rename
> it to AttributeLevel { kNone, kSession, kMedia } so it can be reused.
>
> Migrates extmap-allow-mixed to the new type:
>   ExtmapAllowMixed              -> AttributeLevel
>   kNo                           -> kNone
>   set_extmap_allow_mixed_enum() -> set_extmap_allow_mixed_level()
>   extmap_allow_mixed_enum()     -> extmap_allow_mixed_level()
>
> No (intended) behavior change.
> A follow-up CL will use AttributeLevel for cryptex.
>
